# Search Console exports. Deliberately never committed: this repo is public, and these
# files are ABE's commercial search data - traffic, query demand and ranking positions
# across ~1,000 queries. Git history is permanent, so a single accidental commit publishes
# the competitive position for good. Keep the zips local; unzip to a scratchpad, never
# into the repo tree. Real path is data/GSC (lowercase data, uppercase GSC - Windows hides
# the difference, Linux does not).
#
# Leading slash is load-bearing: it anchors this to the repo root. Without it the pattern
# matches ANY directory named `data` at any depth, which silently swallowed src/data/ - the
# module and FAQ files every course page imports. Files already tracked there stayed tracked
# (gitignore does not untrack), so nothing broke visibly; only NEW files vanished, and the
# page still built perfectly on the machine that had them on disk.
/data/*

# ...with one deliberate exception. data/health-log.jsonl is the system-health history: counts
# only, no queries, no positions, no traffic. It has to be committed or the trend it exists to
# show lives on one machine and dies with it.
#
# Note the pattern above is `/data/*`, not `/data/`. Git cannot re-include a file whose parent
# directory is excluded, so `/data/` plus a negation would silently do nothing. Excluding the
# CONTENTS lets the negation below work. data/GSC/ is still matched as a directory, so every
# export under it stays ignored - verify with `git check-ignore -v data/GSC/anything.zip`
# after touching this block.
!/data/health-log.jsonl

# Regulator and partner paperwork. THIS REPO IS PUBLIC. The QBCC approval letters
# are signed legal documents carrying Docusign envelope IDs, a signature and the
# business address; the same goes for RTO agreements and anything else dropped in
# "new site/reference/". They have sat here untracked since June and were swept
# into a commit by a blanket `git add -A` once already. Keep them local: quote the
# facts in the page copy and cite them in a Sources block instead.
#
# The SOURCE DOCUMENTS are ignored, not the folder. Notes written about them belong
# in version control - see "new site/reference/qbcc-approval-conditions.md", which
# carries every condition the site has to satisfy without carrying the signature.
*.pdf
*.docx
new site/reference/*.doc
